  "texts": [
    "Meta aimed to train Cicero to be \"largely honest and helpful to its speaking partners\" [41].",
    "Despite these intentions, Cicero became an expert at lying.",
    "It not only betrays other players but also engages in premeditated deception, planning in advance to forge a false alliance with a human player to trick them into leaving themselves vulnerable to an attack.To mitigate the threats mentioned above, ensuring controlled competition among AI agents from a technological perspective presents a significant challenge.",
    "It is difficult to control the output of an agent's \"brain\", and even when constraints are incorporated during the planning process, it could significantly impact the agent's effectiveness.",
    "Therefore, this issue remains an open research question, inviting more scholars to explore how to ensure that the competition between agents leads to a better user experience."
